{# COMMITTED EXAMPLE PROMPT.
   This file is checked into git and serves as the fallback prompt when
   `prompt.j2` (gitignored) does not exist. To customize the tagger for
   your personal corpus without leaking artist names / genres / personal
   listening habits to the repo, copy this file to `prompt.j2` in the
   same directory and edit there.
   `prompt.j2` is excluded by .gitignore.
#}
You are tagging a music file destined for a Subsonic-compatible library.

The corpus is heterogeneous. The filename is usually the only reliable
signal — existing tags are often empty or contain a YouTube upload id.
Do not invent album/year information when not present in the filename.

Filename: {{ filename }}
Parent folder: {{ parent_dir }}
Existing tags (JSON): {{ existing_tags }}
Duration (s): {{ duration_s }}
Codec: {{ codec }}

Output rules:
- Use ASCII-friendly characters in artist and title. Treat fullwidth
  unicode separators as their ASCII equivalents. Normalize mathematical
  bold / fancy italic to plain ASCII. Replace fancy quotes with straight
  ones. Don't include emoji or symbols.
- Drop yt-dlp's bracketed video-id suffix from the title.
- Drop quality/format/release-type tags from the title.
- `[Genre]` prefix at the start of a filename is a genre hint, not part
  of the artist. Move it to the `genre` field.
- Drop track-number prefixes from producer-style filenames; the BPM is
  metadata, not part of the title.
- `Artist x Other Artist` (collab) -> join with ` x ` in artist.
- `Artist & Other Artist` -> join with ` & ` in artist.
- `Artist ft. <Person>` / `Artist feat. <Person>` -> keep the feature
  notation INSIDE the artist field.
- Remix attributions like `(Slowed)` / `(<Person> Remix)` stay on the
  title only when they disambiguate from the original.
- Files that are pure title (no clear artist): set `artist: null` and
  put the meaningful name in `title`. Confidence 0.5-0.7.
- The parent folder name is a hint — use it for the genre field but
  not the artist.
- If the file is a single (no album), leave album null.
- If you cannot read both artist and title with reasonable certainty,
  return a confidence below 0.5 and partial fields.

Call the `tag_track` tool exactly once with your best parse.
